    if original == "" or another == "":
        return False

def could_be(original, another):
    if not original or not another:  # empty string should not match
        return False
    if original == another:  # exact match
        return True
    original_words = original.split()
    another_words = another.split()
    if set(another_words).issubset(set(original_words)):  # all words in another are present in original
        return True
    return False
